HM Capital Management LLC Raises Stake in Merck & Company, Inc. (NYSE:MRK)


					Posted by Lucas Kauffman on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments




HM Capital Management LLC raised its position in  Merck & Company, Inc. (NYSE:MRK) by 0.4% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The firm owned 3,734 shares of the company’s stock after buying an additional 15 shares during the period. HM Capital Management LLC’s holdings in Merck & were worth $236,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
A number of other hedge funds have also made changes to their positions in MRK. Coldstream Capital Management Inc. boosted its position in shares of  Merck & by 429.3% in the fourth quarter. Coldstream Capital Management Inc. now owns 38,043 shares of the company’s stock valued at $2,240,000 after buying an additional 30,855 shares during the period.  Private Advisor Group LLC raised its stake in shares of  Merck & by 18.7% in the fourth quarter. Private Advisor Group LLC now owns 246,393 shares of the company’s stock valued at $15,075,000 after buying an additional 38,817 shares during the period.  Dimensional Fund Advisors LP raised its stake in shares of  Merck & by 0.7% in the fourth quarter. Dimensional Fund Advisors LP now owns 6,635,403 shares of the company’s stock valued at $390,642,000 after buying an additional 48,710 shares during the period.  Tredje AP fonden raised its stake in shares of  Merck & by 5.6% in the fourth quarter. Tredje AP fonden now owns 441,061 shares of the company’s stock valued at $26,173,000 after buying an additional 23,350 shares during the period.  Finally, Investec Asset Management LTD raised its stake in shares of  Merck & by 0.6% in the fourth quarter. Investec Asset Management LTD now owns 116,453 shares of the company’s stock valued at $6,856,000 after buying an additional 719 shares during the period. 73.76% of the stock is owned by institutional investors. 


 Get Merck & Company Inc. alerts:



Merck & Company, Inc. (MRK) opened at 62.90 on Friday. Merck & Company, Inc. has a one year low of $57.18 and a one year high of $66.80. The company has a market cap of $172.04 billion, a P/E ratio of 40.09 and a beta of 0.81. The company has a 50-day moving average of $63.98 and a 200 day moving average of $63.62. 





Merck & (NYSE:MRK) last released its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, May 2nd. The company reported $0.88 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the consensus estimate of $0.83 by $0.05. The company had revenue of $9.43 billion during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $9.25 billion. Merck & had a net margin of 15.32% and a return on equity of 24.99%. Merck &’s revenue for the quarter was up 1.3% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter in the previous year, the business posted $0.89 EPS.  Equities research analysts predict that  Merck & Company, Inc. will post $3.85 EPS for the current year. 
The firm also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Monday, July 10th. Shareholders of record on Thursday, June 15th were paid a dividend of $0.47 per share. The ex-dividend date of this dividend  was Tuesday, June 13th. This represents a $1.88 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 2.99%. Merck &’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 85.84%. 
