Company Overview of HM Capital Partners LLC



Snapshot People




Company Overview
HM Capital Partners LLC is a private equity firm specializing in turnarounds, buyouts, industry consolidation, recapitalization and change capital investments in middle market and mature companies. It seeks to invest in the acquisition of under-managed, under-capitalized, or under-appreciated assets; acquisition of divisions or products that have no management; acquisition of divisions or assets of large corporations; acquisition of distressed businesses going either through a restructuring or bankruptcy process; acquisition or recapitalization of privately owned or publicly traded businesses; growth opportunities; and complementary acquisitions. The firm typically invests in media, consumer...
HM Capital Partners LLC is a private equity firm specializing in turnarounds, buyouts, industry consolidation, recapitalization and change capital investments in middle market and mature companies. It seeks to invest in the acquisition of under-managed, under-capitalized, or under-appreciated assets; acquisition of divisions or products that have no management; acquisition of divisions or assets of large corporations; acquisition of distressed businesses going either through a restructuring or bankruptcy process; acquisition or recapitalization of privately owned or publicly traded businesses; growth opportunities; and complementary acquisitions. The firm typically invests in media, consumer products, energy, food and beverages, financial services sector, information services sector, and niche manufacturing sector. In the media sector, it focuses on new media technologies, groups of assets that could benefit from consolidation, and undermanaged proven media assets. Within the energy sector, the firm focuses on on-shore United States natural gas value chain both upstream and downstream, and new capital projects or strategic acquisitions. In the food and beverages sector, it focuses on undermanaged or no management situations, as in the case of a divestiture of a single brand or product line and businesses. The firm prefers to invest in companies based in Europe, Latin America, and North America including the United States. It typically invests in transactions valued between $100 million and above $1 billion. The firm prefers to make control investments. HM Capital Partners LLC was founded in 1989 and is based in Dallas, Texas.
