HM Capital Management LLC Purchases New Position in Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. (The) (NYSE:HIG)

					Posted by Samantha Guadardo on Jul 26th, 2017 // No Comments 


Tweet












HM Capital Management LLC purchased a new stake in shares of  Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. (The) (NYSE:HIG) during the second quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the SEC. The firm purchased 3,900 shares of the insurance provider’s stock, valued at approximately $205,000. 
A number of other hedge funds also recently made changes to their positions in HIG. Marathon Asset Management LLP increased its stake in shares of  Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. (The) by 12.4% in the first quarter. Marathon Asset Management LLP now owns 755,422 shares of the insurance provider’s stock valued at $36,457,000 after buying an additional 83,209 shares in the last quarter.  Capstone Asset Management Co. increased its stake in shares of  Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. (The) by 4.5% in the first quarter. Capstone Asset Management Co. now owns 51,165 shares of the insurance provider’s stock valued at $2,460,000 after buying an additional 2,200 shares in the last quarter.  Spirit of America Management Corp NY increased its stake in shares of  Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. (The) by 7.1% in the first quarter. Spirit of America Management Corp NY now owns 15,000 shares of the insurance provider’s stock valued at $721,000 after buying an additional 1,000 shares in the last quarter.  Bank of Montreal Can increased its stake in shares of  Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. (The) by 30.8% in the first quarter. Bank of Montreal Can now owns 307,483 shares of the insurance provider’s stock valued at $14,781,000 after buying an additional 72,432 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Quadrant Capital Group LLC increased its stake in shares of  Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. (The) by 0.4% in the first quarter. Quadrant Capital Group LLC now owns 2,293 shares of the insurance provider’s stock valued at $106,000 after buying an additional 10 shares in the last quarter. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  89.81% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Hartford Financial Services Group Inc. (The) alerts:



Shares of Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. (NYSE:HIG) traded down 0.85% during trading on Wednesday, hitting $53.48. 812,046 shares of the stock traded hands. The firm has a 50 day moving average price of $52.28 and a 200-day moving average price of $49.46. Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. has a one year low of $38.92 and a one year high of $54.20. The company has a market cap of $19.65 billion, a PE ratio of 21.75 and a beta of 0.93. 




Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. (The) (NYSE:HIG) last posted its earnings results on Thursday, April 27th. The insurance provider reported $1.00 earnings per share for the quarter, missing the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $1.02 by $0.02. The business had revenue of $4.66 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $4.90 billion. Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. (The) had a net margin of 5.12% and a return on equity of 7.48%. The business’s revenue was up 5.6% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the previous year, the firm earned $0.78 EPS.  Analysts anticipate that  Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. will post $4.15 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The company also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Monday, October 2nd. Shareholders of record on Friday, September 1st will be given a $0.23 dividend. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, August 30th. This represents a $0.92 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 1.71%. Hartford Financial Services Group, Inc. (The)’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is presently 37.70%. 
