As President and Co‐Founder of HM Capital Management, Matt is primarily responsible for the overall strategic direction of the Firm and oversight of Institutional and Family Advisory Clients

Matt has over twenty years of investment advisory experience and was Senior Vice President–Institutional Consulting at Wachovia Securities prior to establishing HM Capital Management. Prior to entering the investment advisory industry, Matt was Vice President in the corporate banking departments of Mark Twain Banks and Boatmen’s Banks.
Matt earned his BSBA from Creighton University with an emphasis in Accounting and Finance.
Matt is a long standing member of the Investment Management Consultants Association ® (IMCA).
Matt has been very active in the community having served on numerous boards including the Development Board of Children’s Hospital (member of the finance committee), St. Louis County Highway & Traffic Commission, Kilo Foundation and St. Patrick Center.
Matt and his wife Mary have four children Colin, Cady, Cameron and Chloe.




